column5: Hi All,  Just thought I would drop a little report from my kawartha lake dam tour... Headed out for a few hours and managed to land 2 fish, snapped of 1 and lost 2. They weren't very big but it I had a great time. Here are some pics. (Again, nothing to brag about LOL) Heading out again tonight, with hopefully a little more luck!
That second Wall-ic is a pretty nice fish!... What are you doing with all those clothes and that Toque on???... Do you have the air conditioner turned down too low?
I got pretty cold out there.. Hat, sweater, jacket in August= no sense at all. I was cold! LOL
Nice dam walleyes..!!!!!!!! looks like its gonna be a fish dinner..lol..lol oh ya    what time will that be???????    cheers
Hmmmmmmmmm. walleye,  YUM>   Looks like perfect eating size.  good for you.
Good stuff Grant, glad to see you getting out on your holidays  Maureen
Couple nice fish there Grant, sounds like a fun way to spend a few hours to me.  Good luck tonight.
Recipes are running through my head looking at them....Nice catch and good luck tonight
sounds like someone is getting a little fresh
